As the village grew in size it became necessary to build a new school.It was opened in 1967 and was called Bradwell Junior School. Homefield became the infant school.
{"We had a magazine called the Hungry {Hill News. It was called this because {the school had been built on a field {known as the hungry hill."}
In 1976 Woodlands Middle School was opened. The two other schools became first schools, Bradwell Junior becoming Hillside First. { { "I remember the day we changed {schools. Every child carried something {and we walked from Hillside to {Woodlands in one enormous crocodile."
